node.text:
Does it ever feel like there aren’t enough hours in a day to accomplish everything you hope to accomplish? 

While balancing work and life in a 24-hour period can be a tricky act, there are simple steps you can take to make your daily routine more manageable in order to achieve more in the short term and long term. Join @dorieclark, an industry expert, author, and speaker, for this webinar to hear her insights into how to make the most of your day, every day. Hosted by @itsterryrice. Link in bio to register.

node.title: Webinar: How To Make The Most Out Your 24 Hours

node.text: "Used-to-be’s don't make no honey. So don't nobody care what you used to be!" — artist, TV personality, and founder @kandi tells Entrepreneur's @heyfeifer the philosophy that keeps her going. Don't rest when things go well. Don't give up when things go badly. No matter what, just keep moving!

node.text: Comedian @nikkiglaser has built a career on being unapologetically honest and herself. node.text:
Many founders (if not all founders) experience self-doubt. So how do you keep going when the voices around you (and sometimes in your head) are telling you that you're on a fast track to failure?

@nicolewalters, founder and CEO of @inheritlearning, chats with @nicolegibbonsstyle, founder and CEO of @clarepaint, about overcoming self-doubt when starting a business. (Brought to you by @delltech)

node.title: Building Confidence While Building Your Business

Jason Griffin Reidel, CEO of @gorjana, discusses founding and launching a dream project. Link in bio for full article.

node.text:
Does it ever feel like there aren’t enough hours in a day to accomplish everything you hope to accomplish? 

While balancing work and life in a 24-hour period can be a tricky act, there are simple steps you can take to make your daily routine more manageable in order to achieve more in the short term and long term. Join @dorieclark, an industry expert, author, and speaker, for this webinar to hear her insights into how to make the most of your day, every day. Hosted by @itsterryrice. Link in bio to register.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneur on September 02, 2021 tagging @mariasharapova. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: "When I had a year and a half off from the game, I took a few courses at Harvard Business School and was never so intimidated in my life," says tennis star @mariasharapova. "I was intimidated to raise my hand and ask a question, because I didn’t know a lot of the answers. But once I got comfortable not being the smartest one in the room, the fact that I was learning and growing was so fulfilling." Read more about what losing has taught Sharapova about winning, link in bio.

node.text:
Have you been dreaming of starting your own business but aren’t sure how to begin? 

Being an entrepreneur isn't easy, and it’s not for everyone. Join our LIVE webinar with award-winning entrepreneur and business coach @kimperell, to find out if it's right for you!

This is your chance to learn from the expert: Kim Perell is an award-winning entrepreneur, top US female angel investor, and best selling author with two decades of experience helping others make the jump into entrepreneurship! 

This webinar will teach you the truth about entrepreneurship that no one tells you and the integral steps needed to make the jump from employee to entrepreneur.

Thursday, September 9th @ 12PM EST / 3PM EST. Click the link in bio to register today.

node.text: For @francoisreihani, one revelation changed everything: “I had, frankly, become a dick,” he says. “Like, I wasn’t being a good person.” Reihani was only a teenager at the time, but once he saw himself clearly, he knew he had to make a change. So he took action —­ setting himself on a course for a new life in a new city, and ultimately building a company that stands by one simple slogan: “Don’t be a dick.” Read more about Reihani's journey to starting @lalalandkindcafe in our link in bio.
